FYI : How To Schedule Routine Tasks in PowerShell ?

Automating PowerShell command line.  With help of ‘Get-History’ Command.

This command generates history of commands used.

Steps….

1)	Start the session [open the PowerShell command line]  
2)	Start doing your work [i.e. executing the commands] 
3)	Once done get the history of the commands                   (Get-History).CommandLine | Export-Csv c:\dil.psm1
4)	Go to the path specified and Script is ready.



Regards
